## Project Structure

```
/opt/kesiyos-bot/
├── app/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── main.py                # FastAPI entry point, lifespan, /health endpoint
│   ├── config.py              # Pydantic Settings — loads .env, validates config
│   ├── webhooks.py            # Meta webhook receiver (GET verify + POST messages)
│   ├── agent.py               # Claude API — classify intent + generate response
│   ├── sender.py              # Reply via Meta Graph API (Messenger + IG)
│   ├── escalation.py          # WhatsApp alerts to staff (Tier 2/3)
│   ├── knowledge_base.md      # Complete restaurant knowledge base
│   │
│   ├── db/
│   │   ├── __init__.py
│   │   ├── engine.py          # Async SQLAlchemy engine + session factory
│   │   ├── models.py          # ORM models (4 tables)
│   │   └── migrations/        # Alembic setup (stamped manual_v1)
│   │
│   └── odoo/
│       ├── __init__.py
│       └── connector.py       # XML-RPC interface (stubbed for Phase 2)
│
├── .env                       # Secrets (never committed)
├── .env.example               # Template with all required variables
├── .gitignore
├── alembic.ini
├── kesiyos-bot.service        # systemd unit file
├── nginx-kesiyos-bot.conf     # Nginx proxy config snippet
├── requirements.txt
└── setup.sh                   # One-shot server setup script
```

---

## Database Schema

The agent uses its own PostgreSQL database (`kesiyos_bot`), completely separate from the Odoo database.

### Tables

**`conversations`** — One per customer thread
- Platform (messenger/instagram), sender ID, customer name
- Status: active → escalated → resolved
- Current classification tier and intent category

**`messages`** — Individual messages within conversations
- Direction (inbound/outbound), sender type (customer/bot/human)
- Claude classification metadata (JSONB)
- Unique `platform_message_id` for deduplication

**`escalations`** — Records when staff intervention is needed
- Tier (2 or 3), reason, collected data (JSONB)
- Staff notification timestamps, resolution tracking

**`odoo_sync_queue`** — Bridge to Odoo (Phase 2)
- Sync type: `sale_order`, `reservation`, `new_contact`
- Structured payload (JSONB), retry logic
- Status: pending → synced / failed

---

## Setup

### Prerequisites

- Python 3.10+
- PostgreSQL (same server as Odoo or standalone)
- Nginx (for reverse proxy)
- Meta Developer account with Messenger + Instagram webhook subscriptions
- Anthropic API key
- WhatsApp Cloud API access (for staff escalation only)

### Installation

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone git@github.com:rkingkong/kesiyos-bot.git /opt/kesiyos-bot

# Run the setup script (creates venv, installs deps, sets up directories)
cd /opt/kesiyos-bot
chmod +x setup.sh
sudo ./setup.sh
```

### Configuration

Copy the example environment file and fill in your credentials:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
nano .env
```

Required variables:

| Variable | Description |
|----------|-------------|
| `DATABASE_URL` | PostgreSQL connection string for `kesiyos_bot` database |
| `META_APP_SECRET` | From Meta Developer Dashboard → App Settings |
| `META_VERIFY_TOKEN` | Any random string — must match webhook subscription |
| `META_PAGE_ACCESS_TOKEN` | From Meta Developer Dashboard → Messenger Settings |
| `META_PAGE_ID` | Your Facebook Page ID |
| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | From console.anthropic.com |
| `WHATSAPP_ACCESS_TOKEN` | For sending staff escalation alerts |
| `WHATSAPP_PHONE_NUMBER_ID` | WhatsApp number registered for Cloud API |
| `ESCALATION_STAFF_PHONES` | Comma-separated staff phone numbers (with country code) |

### Nginx

Add the location block from `nginx-kesiyos-bot.conf` to your Nginx server config:

```bash
sudo cp nginx-kesiyos-bot.conf /etc/nginx/snippets/kesiyos-bot.conf
# Then include it in your server block, or merge manually
sudo nginx -t && sudo systemctl reload nginx
```

### Start the Service

```bash
sudo systemctl enable --now kesiyos-bot
sudo systemctl status kesiyos-bot

# Check logs
sudo journalctl -u kesiyos-bot -f
# or
tail -f /var/log/kesiyos-bot/app.log
```

### Meta Webhook Subscription

1. Go to [Meta Developer Dashboard](https://developers.facebook.com) → your app → Webhooks
2. Subscribe to **Messenger** webhooks: `messages`, `messaging_postbacks`
3. Subscribe to **Instagram** webhooks: `messages`
4. Callback URL: `https://kesiyos.com/meta/webhook`
5. Verify token: same value as `META_VERIFY_TOKEN` in your `.env`

